# Gmail OAuth2 Configuration
# 
# To use this example, you need to:
# 1. Create a Google Cloud project at https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Enable the Gmail API
# 3. Create OAuth2 credentials (Desktop application)
# 4. Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# Your Gmail address
GMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com

# OAuth2 Access Token (obtained from OAuth2 flow)
# You can get this by running: npm run auth
GMAIL_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-access-token-here

# Optional: OAuth2 Client credentials for token refresh
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
GOOGLE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your-refresh-token
